article.description: — Almar Atlason's 18 points helped Bradley defeat Tarleton State 86-63 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Bradley earns 86-63 victory against Tarleton State
article.linkText: Bradley earns 86-63 victory against Tarleton State
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- — Almar Atlason's 18 points helped Bradley defeat Tarleton State 86-63 on Tuesday night. Atlason shot 6 for 8, including 6 for 7 from beyond the arc for the Braves (3-0). Christian Davis added 16 points while going 6 of 9 (4 for 6 from 3-point range). Malevy Leons added 13 points. The Texans (2-2) were led in scoring by Lue Williams, who finished with 16 points, six rebounds and five steals. Bubu Benjamin added 16 points for Tarleton State. In addition, Jakorie Smith had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
